    <h3 {...{
      "id": "what-is-detox-and-why-should-you-pick-it"
    }}>{`What is Detox, and why should you pick it?`}</h3>
    <p>{`Detox is an end-to-end framework for mobile apps developed by `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://www.wix.engineering/",
        "target": "_blank",
        "rel": "noreferrer"
      }}>{`Wix`}</a>{`, one of the top contributors inside the React Native community. They also maintain amazing projects such as `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`react-native-navigation`}</inlineCode>{` and `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`react-native-ui-lib`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`What I like about this framework is the great abstraction it provides to select and trigger actions on elements. This is how a normal test looks:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-javascript"
      }}>{`describe('Login flow', () => {
  it('should login successfully', async () => {
    await device.reloadReactNative();
    // getting the reference of an element by ID and expecting to be visible
    await expect(element(by.id('email'))).toBeVisible();

    // Getting the reference and typing
    await element(by.id('email')).typeText('john@example.com');
    await element(by.id('password')).typeText('123456');

    // Getting the reference and executing a tap/press
    await element(by.text('Login')).tap();

    await expect(element(by.text('Welcome'))).toBeVisible();
    await expect(element(by.id('email'))).toNotExist();
  });
});
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`As you can see, the syntax is quite readable, and by using async/await, you can write synchronous and easy-to-understand tests. Let‚Äôs jump into the demo!`}</p>
